President Biden met with NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg to discuss the upcoming NATO Summit in Brussels. They emphasized the importance of building on NATO's success in safeguarding transatlantic security and democratic values. They also discussed the NATO 2030 initiative to adapt the Alliance to address strategic competition and transnational threats such as climate change and cyberattacks. The leaders reviewed progress in boosting defense spending and other contributions to defense, highlighting the need for equitable sharing of responsibility within NATO. They also discussed NATO's investment in Afghanistan and continued support for peace efforts.